<br>
Arkainium - Level 7 HIE Wizard (Zebuxoruk Server) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/25/01 10:13:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddalan.com/~berglund/ikp_hao.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Quests</span><hr size=1> Qeynos is the best place for starting wizards for quests. Do the Qbert, and Ring of Rodcet Nife quests. All doable at your level.<br>
<br>
Ring of Rodcet Nife +3 Int, +10 mana<br>
Golden Ear Stud +3 int<br>
<br>
Free +9 Int<br>
<br>
Best bet is to hop a port to Tox, and then take the ship to Qeynos. Safe, and well worth the trip. Though getting Temple of Life faction is a pain, best bet is the Blessed oil quest. Tedious but the best way to raise faction. The Bone Chip, and Gold don't equal it, and I spent 50pp and still no increase worth mentioning.<br>
<br>
A good strategy is to get to apprehensive, then turn in rabid pelts. Takes 3 grizzlies, or about 6 wolves to get to amiable. Then it's a mule SK to your ring. Another note, is the ring is a random for prayer beads, I kept the prayer beads instead of destroying them. Since both items are lore, the next fish got me my ring.<br>
<br>
Also note that the beads have 2 charges of healing, nice quest for those bad pulls when you get pummelled. Bind to 50%, then use the beads. Head back whenever you need more healing items. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A> at: 8/25/01 10:40:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/01 9:30:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Quests</span><hr size=1> That's for sure.  I did both of those - still wear one of my golden ear studs at lvl 29.  When I grew up there they were selling for 40pp, so you can probably make some good cash with that quest, too. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
